==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interline
<hw>In`ter*line"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Interlined</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Interlining</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>inter-</ets> + <ets>line</ets>: cf. LL. <ets>interlineare</ets>, F.
<ets>interlin⟦eacute⟧er</ets>, OF. <ets>entreligner</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To write or insert between lines already written or
printed, as for correction or addition; to write or print something
between the lines of; <as>as, to <ex>interline</ex> a page or a
book</as>.</def> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To arrange in alternate lines; <as>as, to
<ex>interline</ex> Latin and English</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To mark or imprint with lines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A crooked wrinkle <qex>interlines</qex> my brow.</q>
<rj><qau>Marlowe.</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Interlinear</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Interlineal</ent>⟦br⟧
